2014th%20Amendment%20of%20the%20US%20Constitution%2C%20means%20that%20anyone%20born%20within%20American%20borders%20automatically%20becomes%20a%20citizen%20of%20the%20United%20States.%20This%20includes%20children%20of%20tourists%2C%20students%20studying%20in%20American%20colleges%20on%20short-term%20visas%20and%20undocumented%20immigrants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20incoming%20President%20were%20to%20try%20and%20change%20the%20law%20using%20%26quot%3Bexecutive%20action%26quot%3B%20after%20he%20takes%20office%2C%20it%20would%20undo%20150%20years%20of%20how%20the%20US%20treated%20the%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20did%20Donald%20Trump%20Say%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20first%20formal%20television%20interview%20on%20Sunday%20since%20the%20Presidential%20election%2C%20Mr%20Trump%20was%20asked%20if%20he%20was%20planning%20to%20go%20ahead%20with%20his%20poll%20promise%20of%20ending%20birthright%20citizenship%2C%20to%20which%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BYeah%2C%20absolutely.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20going%20to%20end%20that%20because%20it's%20ridiculous%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20during%20an%20interview%20on%20NBC's%20%26quot%3BMeet%20the%20Press%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20President-elect%20said%20he's%20planning%20on%20changing%20the%20practice%20using%20executive%20action%2C%20noting%20that%20there%20are%20other%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20small%20olive%20branch%20offering%20to%20those%20advocating%20for%20allowing%20some%20undocumented%20migrants%20--%20a%20key%20source%20of%20labour%20for%20much%20of%20the%20US%20economy%20--%20to%20stay%2C%20Mr%20Trump%20said%20he%20will%20%26quot%3Bwork%20with%20the%20Democrats%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bdreamers%26quot%3B%20--%20the%20immigrants%20who've%20become%20successful%20residents%20by%20getting%20good%20jobs%20and%20starting%20businesses%20after%20entering%20the%20United%20States%20illegally%20as%20young%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20breaking%20up%20families%2C%20so%20the%20only%20way%20you%20don't%20break%20up%20the%20family%20is%20you%20keep%20them%20together%20and%20you%20have%20to%20send%20them%20all%20back%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20If%20the%20Trump%20administration%20goes%20ahead%20with%20this%20plan%2C%20it%20would%20mean%20expelling%20legal%20US%20citizens%2C%20including%20those%20who%20got%20citizenship%20through%20birth%2C%20so%20that%20they%20are%20not%20separated%20from%20their%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20Republicans%2C%20including%20Mr%20Trump%2C%20have%20argued%20that%20birthright%20citizenship%20gives%20rise%20to%20%26quot%3Bbirth%20tourism%26quot%3B%2C%20in%20which%20pregnant%20women%20from%20other%20countries%20enter%20the%20US%20illegally%2C%20or%20on%20tourist%20visas%2C%20to%20give%20birth%20there%2C%20before%20returning%20to%20their%20home%20countries.%20This%20way%2C%20their%20children%20are%20born%20US%20citizens.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Does%20The%20Law%20Say%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBirthright%20citizenship%20is%20a%20legal%20principle%20under%20the%2014th%20Amendment%20to%20the%20US%20Constitution.%20This%20principle%20was%20confirmed%20in%20the%20US%20Constitution%20in%201868%2C%20after%20the%20four%20years%20of%20the%20American%20Civil%20War%2C%20to%20overturn%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20decision%20Dred%20Scott%20v.%20Sandford%2C%20which%20denied%20basic%20rights%20to%20African%20Americans.%20The%20judgement%20said%20that%20enslaved%20people%20were%20not%20US%20citizens%20and%2C%20therefore%2C%20could%20not%20expect%20any%20protection%20from%20the%20federal%20government%20or%20the%20courts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20law%2C%20citizenship%20is%20automatically%20granted%20to%20individuals%20upon%20birth%20on%20US%20soil.%20%26quot%3BAll%20persons%20born%20or%20naturalized%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20and%20subject%20to%20the%20jurisdiction%20thereof%2C%20are%20citizens%20of%20the%20United%20States%20and%20of%20the%20State%20wherein%20they%20reside%2C%26quot%3B%20the%2014th%20Amendment%20states.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20constitution%2C%20birthright%20citizenship%20is%20guaranteed%20to%20children%20born%20on%20US%20soil%2C%20%26quot%3Bregardless%20of%20their%20parent's%20immigration%20or%20citizenship%20status%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20Follow%2C%20No%20Index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.americanimmigrationcouncil.org%2Ftopics%2Fbirthright-citizenship%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Immigration%20Council%3C%2Fa%3E's%20website.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20over%20a%20century%2C%20the%20U.S.%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20interpreted%20the%2014th%20Amendment%20as%20conferring%20U.S.%20citizenship%20automatically%20to%20anyone%20born%20on%20U.S.%20soil%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20employs%20a%20combination%20of%20birthright%20citizenship--%20ancestry-based%20citizenship%20and%20birthplace-based%20citizenship.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBirthplace-based%20citizenship%2C%20which%20grants%20citizenship%20based%20on%20place%20of%20birth%2C%20is%20formally%20referred%20to%20as%20jus%20soli%2C%20a%20Latin%20term%20meaning%20%26quot%3Bright%20of%20the%20soil%26quot%3B%2C%20while%20restricted%20ancestry-based%20citizenship%2C%20referred%20to%20as%20jus%20sanguinis%2C%20%C2%A0extends%20citizenship%20to%20children%20born%20abroad%20to%20US%20citizens%2C%20provided%20statutory%20requirements%20are%20met.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20Can%20Birthright%20Citizenship%20Be%20Halted%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20implement%20any%20changes%20in%20the%20Constitution%2C%20Mr%20Trump's%20administration%20will%20require%20the%20support%20of%20a%20two-thirds%20majority%20in%20both%20chambers%20of%20Congress--%20the%20Senate%20and%20the%20House%20of%20Representatives.%20In%20addition%2C%20the%20amendment%20must%20also%20be%20ratified%20by%20three-fourths%20of%20all%20state%20legislatures%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20Follow%2C%20No%20Index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.independent.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld%2Famericas%2Fus-politics%2Fdonald-trump-end-birthright-citizenship-explained-b2661867.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndependent%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERepublicans%20have%20a%2053%20to%2047%20majority%20in%20the%20Senate%20and%20a%20220%20to%20215%20majority%20in%20the%20House%2C%20meaning%20America's%20grand%20old%20party%20(GOP)%20does%20not%20have%20the%20required%20number%20in%20either%20chamber.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202011%20article%2C%20the%20American%20Immigration%20Council%20noted%20that%20if%20birthright%20citizenship%20is%20ever%20halted%20in%20the%20US%2C%20it%20would%20cause%20parents%20to%20have%20to%20prove%20their%20children's%20citizenship%20status.%20%26quot%3BOur%20birth%20certificates%20are%20proof%20of%20our%20citizenship.%20If%20birthright%20citizenship%20were%20eliminated%2C%20U.S.%20citizens%20could%20no%20longer%20use%20their%20birth%20certificates%20as%20proof%20of%20citizenship%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20council%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Donald%20Trump%20Can%20Do%20To%20End%20It%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20Mr%20Trump%20did%20not%20give%20a%20lot%20of%20details%20on%20how%20he%20was%20planning%20to%20end%20birthright%20citizenship%20in%20his%20interview%2C%20the%20matter%20was%20extensively%20discussed%20in%20a%202023%20post%20on%20his%20campaign%20website.%20According%20to%20a%20report%20by%20the%20Associated%20Press%2C%20the%20website%20said%20Mr%20Trump%20would%20issue%20an%20executive%20order%20on%20the%20first%20day%20of%20his%20presidency%2C%20making%20it%20clear%20that%20federal%20agencies%20%26quot%3Brequire%20that%20at%20least%20one%20parent%20be%20a%20U.S.%20citizen%20or%20lawful%20permanent%20resident%20for%20their%20future%20children%20to%20become%20automatic%20US%20citizens.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPer%20the%20incoming%20President%2C%20the%20executive%20order%20would%20make%20clear%20that%20children%20of%20illegal%20immigrants%20%26quot%3Bshould%20not%20be%20issued%20passports%2C%20Social%20Security%20numbers%2C%20or%20be%20eligible%20for%20certain%20taxpayer-funded%20welfare%20benefits.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20law%20is%20clear%20that%20birthright%20citizenship%20can't%20be%20ended%20by%20executive%20order%20and%20any%20such%20move%20would%20almost%20certainly%20end%20up%20in%20litigation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20Mr%20Trump%20may%20be%20inclined%20to%20take%20a%20shot%20anyway%20through%20the%20courts%2C%20said%20Alex%20Nowrasteh%2C%20vice%20president%20for%20economic%20and%20social%20policy%20studies%20at%20the%20pro-immigration%20Cato%20Institute.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20take%20his%20statements%20very%20seriously.%20He%20has%20been%20saying%20things%20like%20this%20for%20almost%20a%20decade...He%20didn't%20do%20anything%20to%20further%20this%20agenda%20when%20he%20was%20president%20before.%20The%20law%20and%20judges%20are%20near%20uniformly%20opposed%20to%20his%20legal%20theory%20that%20the%20children%20of%20illegal%20immigrants%20born%20in%20the%20United%20States%20are%20not%20citizens%2C%26quot%3B%20Nowrasteh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Trump%20could%20steer%20Congress%20to%20pass%20a%20law%20to%20end%20birthright%20citizenship%20but%20would%20still%20face%20a%20legal%20challenge%20that%20it%20violates%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733907180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2F4ld5u36o_trump_625x300_08_December_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdonald-trump-says-he-will-end-us-birthright-citizenship-but-can-he-7222601%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22US%20President-elect%20Donald%20Trump%20has%20said%20he%20plans%20to%20end%20birth