t%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Fiiofo85o_syria-streets_625x300_08_December_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDamascus%20has%20fallen.%20Once%20again.%20One%20of%20the%20oldest%20cities%20in%20the%20world%20has%20fallen.%20To%20rise%20again%20from%20its%20rubble%2C%20heralding%20a%20new%20order.%20In%20its%20rise%20and%20fall%2C%20Damascus%20has%20lessons%20for%20all%20civilisations%2C%20all%20rebels%2C%20and%20all%20regimes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20in%20July%202012%20that%20rebels%20penetrated%20Damascus%2C%20hitherto%20considered%20inviolable.%20Both%20the%20regime%20and%20the%20rebels%20understood%20its%20importance%E2%80%94military%20and%20symbolic.%20The%20rebels%20advanced%20to%20the%20heavily%20militarised%20capital%20of%20Syria%20but%20did%20not%20make%20any%20real%20gains.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20in%20August%202013%2C%20the%20Syrian%20regime%20launched%20Operation%20Capital%20Shield.%20The%20capital%20had%20to%20be%20shielded%2C%20and%20any%20amount%20of%20force%20was%20acceptable%20to%20thwart%20any%20rebel%20attack.%20The%20city%20was%20safeguarded%20through%20the%20use%20of%20disproportionate%20force%20against%20rebels%20operating%20from%20around%20Damascus.%20Only%20temporarily%20so.%20Eleven%20years%20later%2C%20the%20regime%20has%20fallen.%20For%20the%20sixth%20time%2C%20at%20least%2C%20since%20the%201st%20century%20AD%20Roman%20conquest%20of%20Damascus's%20Seleucid%20empire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Cycle%20Of%20Power%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20has%20Damascus%20seen%20violent%20regime%20changes%2C%20it%20has%20also%20experienced%20ethnic%20and%20religious%20clashes%2C%20including%20the%20Crusades.%20But%20in%20almost%20every%20significant%20clash%E2%80%94civilisational%20or%20political%E2%80%94one%20thing%20has%20stayed%20common%3A%20recapturing%20of%20the%20lost%20ground.%20The%20cyclical%20nature%20of%20power.%20The%20centuries-old%20unabated%20contestation%20on%20the%20socio-political%20turf%20of%20Damascus%20has%20defined%20its%20character.%20The%20current%20developments%20in%20Syria%2C%20therefore%2C%20ought%20to%20be%20examined%20through%20a%20more%20expansive%20glass%20of%20history%20and%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPeter%20Frankopan's%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Silk%20Roads%3C%2Fem%3E%20underscores%20the%20importance%20of%20Damascus%20as%20an%20emporium%20adjacent%20to%20one%20of%20the%20most%20thriving%20trade%20routes%20of%20the%20world.%20Despite%20no%20easy%20access%20to%20the%20Mediterranean%20Sea%2C%20it%20was%20in%20the%20league%20of%20great%20cosmopolitan%20cities%20such%20as%20the%20Byzantine%20Constantinople%20(Istanbul)%2C%20the%20Greco-Roman%20Antioch%2C%20and%20the%20old%20Chinese%20capital%20city%20of%20Chang'an.%20Its%20early%20embrace%20of%20agricultural%20practices%20owing%20to%20the%20natural%20inland%20water%20systems%20of%20the%20Barada%20River%20and%20investments%20in%20irrigation%20infrastructure%20made%20Damascus%20a%20land%20of%20plenty.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20at%20the%20peak%20of%20Christian-Muslim%20religious%20clashes%20around%20the%2010th%20century%20AD%2C%20traders%20had%20a%20breezy%20time%20in%20Damascus.%20Muslim%20traders%20from%20Spain%2C%20for%20example%2C%20were%20protected%20by%20the%20Christians%20of%20Damascus.%20For%20one%20of%20the%20oldest%20inhabited%20cities%20of%20the%20world%2C%20with%20no%20religious%20underpinnings%20originating%20from%20any%20religious%20text%2C%20trade%20was%20vital.%20Traders%2C%20the%20outsiders%2C%20were%20therefore%20immune%20to%20the%20local%20political%20and%20religious%20strife.%20Damascene%20society%20depended%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9Coutsiders%E2%80%9D%20to%20retain%20its%20regional%20power%20as%20a%20seat%20of%20sociocultural%20dominance.%20Damascus%2C%20as%20perceived%20today%2C%20is%20essentially%20a%20result%20of%20four%20centuries%20of%20Ottoman%20rule%20that%20came%20to%20an%20end%20with%20the%20First%20World%20War.%20The%20city%20was%20the%20seat%20of%20the%20Turkish%20Wali.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELands%20Of%20'Outsiders'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDamascus%2C%20curiously%2C%20wasn't%20ruled%20by%20a%20local%20dynasty%20ever%20since%20the%20overthrow%20of%20the%20Aram-Damascus%20kingdom%20in%20the%20eighth%20century%20BC.%20This%20feature%20makes%20Damascus%20closer%20to%20Delhi%20than%20its%20Phoenician%2C%20Judean%2C%20and%20Arab%20neighbours.%20The%20%E2%80%9Coutsiders%E2%80%9D%20soon%20started%20becoming%20the%20insiders%2C%20and%20the%20city%20evolved.%20Delhi%20has%20this%20in%20common%20with%20Damascus%20and%20lessons%20from%20the%20latter%20are%2C%20therefore%2C%20pertinent%20to%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Assad%20regime's%20rise%20and%20fall%20alerts%20us%20to%20the%20limitations%20of%20liberalism%20when%20it%20stays%20within%20the%20elite%20confines.%20It%20is%20always%20prone%20to%20crumbling%20under%20the%20weight%20of%20popular%20mobilisation.%20The%20mainstay%20of%20Syria's%20multicultural%20nature%20was%20consociational%20engagements%20between%20different%20ethno-religious%20groups%20at%20different%20times%20in%20history.%20The%20Assad%20regime's%20politicisation%20of%20the%20Syrian%20society's%20multiculturalism%20was%20self-serving.%20After%20the%20military%20coup%20of%201970%20that%20installed%20Hafez%20al-Assad%20as%20a%20totalitarian%20ruler%2C%20all%20forms%20of%20dissent%20began%20to%20be%20crushed%2C%20ironically%2C%20by%20the%20ruling%20Ba'ath%20Party%2C%20the%20regional%20champion%20of%20dissenters%20in%20the%20Arab%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20liberalism%20gets%20weaponised%20thus%2C%20it%20spells%20doom%20for%20not%20just%20the%20conservatives%20but%20also%20the%20quintessential%20liberal%20values.%20Bashar%20al-Assad%20carried%20forward%20this%20legacy%20of%20his%20father%20with%20more%20zeal%20and%20ruthlessness.%20The%20rebellion%20against%20him%2C%20therefore%2C%20needs%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20not%20only%20political%20but%20also%20socio-religious.%20The%20Sunni%20Muslims%20of%20Syria%2C%20the%20majority%20group%2C%20clearly%20had%20had%20enough%20of%20the%20marginalisation%20heaped%20on%20them%20by%20the%20Alawite%20(Shia)%20Assad%20family%20and%20their%20acolytes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELiberalism%20And%20Liberals%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20should%20appear%20familiar%20to%20us.%20The%20undermining%20of%20liberal%20values%20by%20liberals%20themselves%2C%20the%20ascent%20of%20conservative%20forces%2C%20the%20politics%20of%20exclusion%2C%20and%20the%20many%20fires%20of%20violent%20ethno-religious%20clashes%2C%20we%20have%20seen%20it%20all.%20Politics%20of%20exclusion%2C%20even%20when%20the%20most%20inclusionary%20players%20indulge%20in%20it%2C%20never%20ends%20well.%20The%20civil%20war%20in%20Syria%20needs%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20another%20element%20in%20the%20continuum%20that%20has%20the%20return%20of%20the%20Taliban%20in%20Afghanistan%2C%20the%20Islamic%20Revolution%20of%20Iran%20of%201979%2C%20the%20reactionary%20overthrow%20of%20the%20Kemalist%20order%20in%20Turkey%20by%20Erdogan%2C%20and%20the%20fall%20of%20Sheikh%20Hasina%20in%20Dhaka%20as%20landmark%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImmediately%20after%20the%20fall%20of%20Damascus%2C%20scenes%20of%20celebrations%20(and%20looting)%20started%20flooding%20the%20news%20and%20social%20media.%20Impervious%20to%20them%2C%20Israel%20moved%20to%20plant%20its%20flag%20beyond%20the%20earlier%20buffer%20zone.%20And%20this%20is%20the%20lesson%20Delhi's%20regime%20and%20rebels%20must%20pay%20heed%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Nishtha%20Gautam%20is%20a%20Delhi-based%20author%20and%20academic.)%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733900820000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Fiiofo85o_syria-streets_625x300_08_December_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Flessons-in-liberalism-from-damascus-to-delhi-7222135%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20undermining%20of%20liberal%20values%20by%20liberals%20themselves%2C%20the%20ascent%20of%20conservative%20forces%2C%20the%20politics%20of%20exclusion%2C%20we%20have%20seen%20it%20all.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Flessons-in-liberalism-from-damascus-to-delhi-7222135%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%2050%20men%20accused%20in%20mass%20rape%20of%20Gis%C3%A8le%20Pelicot%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733900729000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2Fdfe9%2Flive%2F48fe7750-b78e-11ef-ae21-3dc17330c1c3.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcr7vvj8gymyo%230%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20men%20accused%20of%20raping%20Gis%C3%A8le%20Pelicot%20have%20been%20dubbed%20Monsieur-Tout-Le-Monde%20as%20they%20broadly%20represent%20a%20microcosm%20of%20French%20society.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A25%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcr7vvj8gymyo%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcr7vvj8gymyo.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcr7vvj8gymyo.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mahindra%20Susten's%20clean-tech%20arm%20secures%20Rs%201%2C448%20crore%20term%20loan%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733900669000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fmahindra-susten-s-clean-tech-arm-secures-rs-1-448-crore-term-loan-124121100352_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20financing%20will%20supp