80%99%20is%20generational%20sharing%2C%20where%20older%20generations%20pass%20down%20their%20knowledge%20of%20food%20and%20recipes%20to%20younger%20people.%20This%20is%20crucial%20in%20a%20time%20when%20traditional%20recipes%20are%20being%20lost%20due%20to%20the%20changing%20dynamics%20of%20family%20structures%20and%20lifestyles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20organise%20%E2%80%98Food%20Culture%20Play%20Dates%E2%80%99%20for%20children%20aged%20between%20seven%20and%2014%2C%20which%20aims%20to%20teach%20children%20about%20the%20importance%20of%20food%20in%20their%20cultural%20heritage.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20train%20the%20kids%20to%20be%20ethnographic%20and%20document%20their%20family%20recipes%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dipali%20explains.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20also%20creates%20this%20sense%20of%20wonder%20%E2%80%94%20what%20was%20the%20food%2C%20and%20where%20is%20it%20coming%20from%3F%20And%20makes%20you%20want%20to%20know%20more.%E2%80%9D%20The%20children%20are%20encouraged%20to%20speak%20to%20their%20family%20members%20about%20the%20food%20they%20ate%20growing%20up%20and%20the%20stories%20around%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FSoni-ji-from-Gaadiya-Lohar-Tribe_11zon-1733392122-500x625.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20clad%20in%20traditional%20banjara%20clothing%2C%20preparing%20her%20mud%20stove%20with%20wood%20fuel.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FSoni-ji-from-Gaadiya-Lohar-Tribe_11zon-1733392122-500x625.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FSoni-ji-from-Gaadiya-Lohar-Tribe_11zon-1733392122-240x300.jpg%20240w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FSoni-ji-from-Gaadiya-Lohar-Tribe_11zon-1733392122-768x960.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FSoni-ji-from-Gaadiya-Lohar-Tribe_11zon-1733392122-150x188.jpg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FSoni-ji-from-Gaadiya-Lohar-Tribe_11zon-1733392122.jpg%201080w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-386570%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22625%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBy%20documenting%20and%20sharing%20these%20recipes%2C%20%E2%80%98The%20Kindness%20Meal%E2%80%99%20is%20helping%20future%20generations%20not%20lose%20touch%20with%20their%20culinary%20heritage.%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDipali%20recalls%20a%20heartwarming%20tale%20from%20one%20of%20their%20sessions%2C%20where%20a%20child%20shared%20her%20father%E2%80%99s%20family%E2%80%99s%20tradition%20of%20drinking%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Ejadi%20ber%20ki%20chai%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20tea%20made%20from%20the%20dried%20fruit%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Eber%20%3C%2Fem%3Etree%2C%20to%20help%20her%20grandmother%20with%20insomnia.%20The%20child%E2%80%99s%20father%20was%20incredibly%20moved%20by%20the%20memory%2C%20as%20he%20realised%20how%20important%20this%20family%20ritual%20had%20been%2C%20and%20how%20it%20had%20slipped%20away%20when%20the%20family%20moved%20to%20Jaipur.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESanjana%20Sarkar%2C%2038%2C%20who%20works%20with%20the%20French%20Embassy%20and%20serves%20as%20the%20director%20of%20Alliance%20Fran%C3%A7aise%2C%20Jaipur%2C%20describes%20herself%20as%20someone%20who%20%E2%80%9Clives%20to%20eat%E2%80%9D.%20During%20one%20of%20the%20Food%20Culture%20Play%20Dates%2C%20children%20from%20various%20schools%2C%20diverse%20in%20terms%20of%20financial%20backgrounds%2C%20came%20together.%20%E2%80%9COn%20the%20first%20day%2C%20we%20noticed%20that%20when%20asked%20about%20what%20type%20of%20food%20they%20like%2C%20they%20all%20had%20a%20common%20preference%20for%20processed%20and%20packaged%20foods%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20recalls%3B%20%E2%80%9CBut%20the%20next%20day%2C%20when%20they%20came%20with%20their%20stories%20about%20%3Cem%3Eber%20ki%20chai%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Rajasthani%20plum%20tea)%20and%20%3Cem%3Elehsun%20ki%20kheer%20%3C%2Fem%3E(Garlic%20rice%20pudding)%2C%20the%20curiosity%20was%20palpable.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20two%20day%20workshop%2C%20they%20made%20a%20binder%20with%20all%20the%20traditional%20recipes%20shared%20by%20the%20children.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20binder%20is%20kept%20in%20our%20library%20here%2C%20and%20we%E2%80%99ve%20archived%20those%20recipes%20to%20do%20our%20part%20in%20preserving%20this%20rich%20food%20heritage%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20want%20to%20encourage%20children%20to%20enjoy%20their%20own%20home%2C%20community%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F382249%2Fbest-khau-gallis-food-walks-tours-trails-mysuru-mumbai-delhi-kolkata-varanasi-northeast%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estate%E2%80%99s%20food%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20champion%20it%20before%20it%20all%20begins%20to%20look%20and%20taste%20the%20same.%E2%80%9D%20By%20documenting%20and%20sharing%20these%20recipes%2C%20%E2%80%98The%20Kindness%20Meal%E2%80%99%20is%20helping%20future%20generations%20not%20lose%20touch%20with%20their%20culinary%20heritage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHelping%20people%20connect%20to%20their%20roots%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManohar%20Kabeer%20(32)%2C%20a%20communications%20professional%2C%20found%20out%20about%20%E2%80%98The%20Kindness%20Meal%E2%80%99%20when%20a%20friend%20shared%20a%20reel%20of%20theirs.%20%E2%80%9CI%20felt%20as%20though%20I%20was%20the%20beneficiary%20of%20what%20she%20was%20trying%20to%20do%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%20A%20Rajasthani%20who%20grew%20up%20in%20Maharashtra%2C%20Manohar%20was%20taken%20back%20to%20summers%20in%20his%20%3Cem%3Enani%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fem%3E(grandmother)%20house.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20would%20be%20a%20lot%20of%20dishes%20made%20with%20%3Cem%3Ebajra%3C%2Fem%3E%20(pearl%20millets)%2C%20I%20especially%20remember%20the%20%3Cem%3Erabdi%20%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20thickened%2C%20sweetened%20milk%20dish).%20Then%20there%20were%20foraged%20foods%20like%20%3Cem%3Emangodi%20%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20variation%20of%20the%20mung%20bean)%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3Esangri%20%3C%2Fem%3E(desert%20bean)%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethat%20would%20be%20used%20to%20make%20sabzi%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManohar%E2%80%99s%20parents%20moved%20to%20Maharashtra%20in%20the%201990s%2C%20but%20his%20trips%20back%20were%20marked%20by%20the%20food%20they%20ate.%20His%20%3Cem%3Enana%20%3C%2Fem%3E(grandfather)%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eowned%20buffaloes%20and%20camels.%20%E2%80%9CI%20even%20remember%20waking%20up%20to%20the%20sound%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Ebilona%20%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20wooden%20churner%20which%20was%20used%20to%20churn%20curd%20into%20fermented%20makkhan%20or%20butter).%20We%20were%20very%20greedy%20about%20it%2C%20so%20we%E2%80%99d%20eat%20as%20much%20as%20possible%20in%20those%20two%20months%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20fondly%20recalls.%20After%20moving%20out%20and%20living%20alone%2C%20he%20started%20ordering%20Rajasthani%20food%20online%2C%20and%20often%20chose%20%3Cem%3Egatte%20ki%20sabzi%20%3C%2Fem%3E(Gram%20flour%20dumpling%20curry)%2C%20although%20he%20admits%20that%20his%20mother%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20consider%20it%20%E2%80%9Cproper%20food%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEvery%20state%20in%20our%20country%20is%20actually%20a%20country%20in%20itself.%20So%2C%20you%20cannot%20label%20it%20as%20just%20Rajasthani%20food%20or%20Gujarati%20food.%20Every%20community%2C%20culture%2C%20geography%2C%20changes%20every%20few%20kilometres%20and%20we%20need%20to%20start%20speaking%20about%20these%20micro%20cuisines%20sooner%20than%20later%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dipali%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-widt